title: A typical example of variables which are needed in debug builds while unneeded in production are return values indicating success. In the debug builds, the condition should be asserted, though in production these asserts have been removed.

title: A more complex example are different kind of helper functions which are in an unnamed namespace. If these functions aren’t used during compilation, a compiler might give a warning on them. Ideally you would like to guard them with the same preprocessor tags as the caller, though as this might become complex the
[[maybe_unused]]
c
attribute is a more maintainable alternative.
